# .distignore
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files and directories listed here are EXCLUDED from WordPress.org SVN deploys.
# The 10up deploy action uses this list when rsyncing to SVN trunk.
#
# Rule of thumb: exclude anything that is only useful in the GitHub dev context
# and should NOT end up on the 3+ million sites that install your plugin.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Git internals
/.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# GitHub-specific
/.github

# WordPress.org assets folder — the 10up action handles this separately,
# moving it to the top-level SVN /assets/ directory. Do NOT let it land in trunk.
/.wordpress-org

# GitHub-flavored readme (WP.org uses readme.txt, not README.md)
README.md

# This file itself
.distignore

# Node / build tooling (uncomment if you add a build step)
/node_modules
package.json
package-lock.json
.npmrc

# Composer (uncomment if you add PHP dependencies)
/vendor
composer.json
composer.lock

# Tests (uncomment if you add a test suite)
/tests
phpunit.xml
phpunit.xml.dist
.phpunit.result.cache

# Linting / code quality (uncomment if you add these)
phpcs.xml
phpcs.xml.dist
.phpcs.xml
.eslintrc
.stylelintrc

# Local dev / IDE files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.code-workspace
